  "instructions": [
    "In a large slow cooker, combine the rinsed lentils, chopped onion, carrot, and celery.",
    "In a small pan, saute the minced garlic and grated ginger in a little water until fragrant.",
    "Add the sauteed garlic and ginger to the slow cooker.",
    "Stir in the dried tarragon, tomato paste, and vegetable broth.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Cover the slow cooker and cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours.",
    "About 30 minutes before serving, stir in some chopped fresh cilantro if desired.",
    "Serve the dal hot over rice or with some naan bread."
